DOC_LEVEL: L2
MODULE: pipeline/scripts
PATH: dev-pipeline/scripts/**
DESCRIPTION: python automation scripts for feature+bugfix state management and prompt generation

KEY_FILES:
- dev-pipeline/scripts/path_policy.py
- dev-pipeline/scripts/init-dev-team.py
- dev-pipeline/scripts/generate-bootstrap-prompt.py
- dev-pipeline/scripts/generate-bugfix-prompt.py
- dev-pipeline/scripts/update-feature-status.py
- dev-pipeline/scripts/update-bug-status.py

JS_MIRROR: src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js
PARITY_TESTS: tests/pipeline-infra/path-policy-python-compat.test.js

PATH_POLICY:
- feature slug: ###-kebab-case via compute_feature_slug
- feature session status: dev-pipeline/state/features/{id}/sessions/{sessionId}/session-status.json
- bug session status: dev-pipeline/bugfix-state/bugs/{id}/sessions/{sessionId}/session-status.json
- daemon logs: state/pipeline-daemon.log + bugfix-state/pipeline-daemon.log
- specs dir: .prizmkit/specs/{slug}/

TRAPS:
- scripts are invoked by shell wrappers; CLI arg compatibility is required
- avoid introducing implicit relative paths; resolve from project_root
- cleanup flows in update-* scripts must preserve status.json while clearing session artifacts
- path_policy.py must maintain exact parity with JS path-policy.js (see PARITY_TESTS)

DECISIONS:
- 2026-03-10 | f001-shared-python-policy | imported path_policy.py in init/generate/update scripts to remove hardcoded path fragments
- 2026-03-10 | f001-daemon-log-policy | daemon log locations documented and consumed via unified path policy for US2
- 2026-03-12 | f001-js-python-parity | JS path-policy.js mirrors Python path_policy.py with identical behavior for cross-language compatibility
